|CKBCold Signal|000

|CK0Cold Signal is passive thermal-control firmware unlocked with the
torso-mounted Thermal Exchange Manifold. Older systems may still call this
implant the Coolant System. It operates automatically while the implant is
installed and the Street Samurai contract is active. It has no activation
command and no SP, Edge, or Heat cost.|000

|CKBWhat it does|000
|CK0Cold Signal watches new Heat created by firmware. When a burst is large
enough for the coolant loop to help, it vents part of that burst before the
load reaches the Cortex. It also gives the platform more room to operate in
redline before the monitor reports overheat.|000

|CK0Cold Signal does not erase existing Heat, raise maximum Heat, replace
ordinary cooling, or guarantee that a large burst cannot cause lockout. Its
value is sustained thermal control: repeated routines leave less load for the
Cortex to clear.|000

|CKBWhat affects it|000
|CK0Thermal Exchange Manifold grade and maintenance condition influence how
much pressure the passive can handle. Damaged or fragmented hardware still
functions but may vent less. When Cold Signal intervenes, the Cortex reports
the amount of Heat removed from that burst.|000

|CKBChecking the passive|000
|CK0Samskills reports whether the Thermal Exchange Manifold is installed.
Dashboard lists its grade, condition, and COLD SIGNAL state. Samstatus shows
whether the passive is online, while monitor shows the resulting live Heat
band.|000

|CK0Thermal Purge uses the same manifold in reverse to drive a short-range flame
projector. The attack creates Heat normally and does not disable Cold Signal.
In an emergency, "thermalpurge vent" can dump all existing Heat immediately,
including during thermal lockout, but the backwash inflicts severe integrity
wear on both the Cortex OS and Thermal Exchange Manifold.|000

|CK0Cold Signal and Overclock solve different problems. Cold Signal reduces
incoming thermal pressure throughout a fight. Overclock temporarily raises the
thermal ceiling by stressing the Cortex OS. Overdrive handles an engagement's
opening Heat burst.|000
